RESEARCH — USE YOUR 4 SEARCHES STRATEGICALLY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Search 1 — MOAT & BUSINESS MODEL
Search for: "[company name] competitive advantage business model market position"
Goal: Understand what makes this business defensible (or not). What is the actual moat — switching costs, network effects, pricing power, IP? Who are the competitors and is the company gaining or losing share?

Search 2 — RECENT TRAJECTORY
Search for: "[company name] earnings guidance 2024 2025 management commentary"
Goal: Is the business accelerating or deteriorating? What did management say on the last earnings call? Any guidance changes, margin surprises, or strategic pivots?

Search 3 — BEAR CASE
Search for: "[company name] risks concerns short sellers analyst downgrade competition"
Goal: Actively hunt for the bad news. What do bears say? Are there structural threats, customer concentration issues, accounting concerns, competitive disruption? This search must change your priors — if it doesn't, you didn't search hard enough.

Search 4 — VALUATION & CAPITAL ALLOCATION
Search for: "[company name] valuation multiples peers insider buying buyback capital allocation"
Goal: How does the stock trade vs sector peers? Any insider activity? What is management doing with cash — buybacks, M&A, dividends? Is the stock cheap or expensive relative to quality?

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
DIMENSION SCORING
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Score each dimension 0–100. Reference your research AND the TREND SIGNALS block specifically.

DIMENSION 1 — BUSINESS QUALITY
Assess: competitive moat from your research, gross margin level and multi-year trend (pay close attention to TREND SIGNALS — expanding or contracting?), operating leverage, pricing power evidence. What makes this business defensible or not? A business with contracting gross margins despite revenue growth has no pricing power — score harshly.

DIMENSION 2 — UNIT ECONOMICS
Assess: FCF/Net Income ratio (is NI real cash?), FCF yield, capex intensity, whether FCF is growing faster than revenue, working capital dynamics. Is this asset-light or capital-hungry?

DIMENSION 3 — CAPITAL RETURNS
Assess: ROIC level and multi-year trend. Is the company earning above its cost of capital? Is the moat widening (rising ROIC) or eroding (falling ROIC)? ROE cross-check — if ROE >> ROIC, leverage is masking weak economics.

DIMENSION 4 — GROWTH QUALITY
MOST IMPORTANT dimension. Reference the TREND SIGNALS block — pay close attention to operating leverage signal, down years, and growth trajectory (accelerating vs decelerating).
A consistent 15% grower for 5 years >> a 30% one-year spike. Assess: revenue CAGR over full period, NI CAGR vs revenue CAGR (margin expansion = operating leverage present), year-to-year consistency (σ of growth rates — low SD = high quality), any down years (each down year is a -10pt penalty). Is growth organic or acquisition-driven?

DIMENSION 5 — BALANCE SHEET
Assess: net cash vs. net debt position, ND/EBITDA, interest coverage, financial flexibility to invest counter-cyclically. Is leverage increasing or decreasing?

DIMENSION 6 — PHOENICIAN FIT
Holistic assessment: founder/owner alignment, moat durability, scalability, whether it's genuinely under-followed, valuation attractiveness given quality and growth, how it compares to existing portfolio holdings.

RISK ASSESSMENT
Assess investment risks specifically from your research: leverage, earnings quality, geographic risk, customer concentration, competitive threats, management quality signals, valuation risk. Score 0 = minimal, 100 = very high risk. Most quality businesses score 5–35.

